From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] python: fix static Unicode interning failure check

The internal hashtable setter returns zero on success and minus one when an
entry allocation fails.  Treat that documented error as fatal instead of
silently marking a string interned even though it was not inserted.
---
 Objects/unicodeobject.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/Objects/unicodeobject.c b/Objects/unicodeobject.c
--- a/Objects/unicodeobject.c
+++ b/Objects/unicodeobject.c
@@ -15100,7 +15100,7 @@ intern_static(PyInterpreterState *interp, PyObject *s /* stolen */)
         return Py_NewRef(r);
     }
 
-    if (_Py_hashtable_set(INTERNED_STRINGS, s, s) < -1) {
+    if (_Py_hashtable_set(INTERNED_STRINGS, s, s) < 0) {
         Py_FatalError("failed to intern static string");
     }
 
